Step 1: Identify the net profit.
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is 835266.51.

Step 2: Identify the owners’ equity values.
• At the beginning (2023-12-31), Paid-in Capital (which is typically the base for owner’s equity) is 13000000.00.
• At the end (2024-02-05), Total Owner’s Equity is 13835266.51.

Step 3: Calculate the average owner’s equity.
• Average Owner’s Equity = (Beginning Equity + Ending Equity) / 2
• = (13000000.00 + 13835266.51) / 2 = 26835266.51 / 2 = 13417633.255

Step 4: Compute the ROE.
• ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity) × 100%
• = (835266.51 / 13417633.255) × 100% ≈ 0.06225 × 100% ≈ 6.23%

Thus, the Return on Equity (ROE) for the period is approximately 6.23%.
